criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients diagnosed with acute lymphoblastic leukemia who had not previously received
             chemotherapy (except for hormone preconditioning) or started with chemotherapy but not
             more than 3 days, and CMV and EBV quantitative negative;

          2. Age Limits:>or= 14 years old.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who had previously received chemotherapy and hematopoietic stem cell
             transplantation;

          2. Patients with CMV and EBV infection before treatment and not to turn yin;

          3. The researchers considered unsuitable patients.
